                            <p><br /></p>
                            <p>Every day, <b>debris can accumulate on the tongue</b> leading to a somewhat unattractive white coating.</p>
                            <p><br /></p>
                            <p>
                                This white coating can contain <b>bacteria</b> such as <b>Mutans streptococci and Lactobacilli</b>. <i>These bacterias are known to contribute to <b>bad breath</b></i> and a deterioration in oral hygiene that can ultimately affect the health of your teeth and
                                gums.
                            </p>
                            <p><br /></p>
                            <p>A <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/16032940" target="_blank">study in 2005</a> reported that<b> using a <a href="https://amzn.to/3bAMRpV">tongue scraper</a> twice daily for at least 2 minutes decreased the presence of these bacteria by 30%</b> after only 7 days.</p>
