                            <h1>WHAT TYPE OF CARDIO IS BEST FOR WEIGHT LOSS?</h1>
                            <p><br /></p>
                            <p>
                                To lose weight, you will probably have to <b>increase your activity level</b>. However, it’s not that simple.
                            </p><p><br /></p>
                            <p>
                                If you increase your activity level, your body will burn more calories. <b>The calories it chooses to burn will be those that are readily available</b>.
                            </p><p><br /></p>
                            <p>
                                This is why so many people go on calorie-restricting diets. If they restrict their calories enough, then their body will start to <b>burn stored fats</b>.
                            </p><p><br /></p>
                            <p>
                                This is a very bad strategy. <b>The body is tricked into a false sense of food-scarcity.</b>
                            </p><p><br /></p>
                            <p>
                                The body will try to <b>pre-empt</b> these periods of food-scarcity by <b>storing more fat in the future.</b>
                            </p><p><br /></p>
                            <blockquote class="quote">
                                <b>Use cardio to burn this fat</b>, while eating a normal healthy diet.
                            </blockquote><p><br /></p>
                            <p>
                                During a cardiovascular workout, the body is burning calories <v>extremely fast</v>. The ‘<i>readily available</i>’ calories are not enough to deliver the required energy, so <b>more resources are burned to meet the demand</b>.
                            </p><p><br /></p>
                            <p>
                                It is the intensity of the cardio workout that determines how many calories are being burned per unit time. <b>The higher the intensity, the more stored fats are metabolised</b>.
                            </p><p><br /></p>
                            <p>
                                The intensity of a cardiovascular workout is proportional to your heart-rate. <b>For weight loss, the heart rate should be between 60% and 75% of your maximum heart rate</b>.
