                                    <h2>WHY SELF HYPNOSIS?</h2>

                                    <p><br /></p>
                                    <p>Self-hypnosis is a solution for changing our internal constructs. Society forms many of our opinions. Sometimes our nature of <strong>‘contentment’</strong> is not the correct course of action. We can hear new information or learn new ideas that conflict with our learned ideas or behaviours.</p>
                                    <p><br /></p>
                                    <P>In other words, we can learn to live with things the way they are without feeling uncomfortable. If we want to change, it needs to come from higher thinking.</P>
                                    <p><br /></p>
                                    <h5>WHEN SHOULD I USE SELF-HYPNOSIS?</h5>
                                    <p><br /></p>
                                    <p>A good example of the application for self-hypnosis would be any change where the outcome is not the norm, such as veganism. Many people grow up on animal-based diets and grow accustomed to the idea of some animals being robbed of the moral value because their flesh is tasty.</p>
                                    <p><br /></p>
                                    <p>To change the initial mindset is not to listen to the body and the lower cortical regions of the brain. The new ideas for the change are in the higher, rational, and logical, regions of the brain.</p>
                                    <p><br /></p>
                                    <p>Reprogramming our instincts, habits, everyday tendencies, and routine is no simple task. However, we should be prepared to do it, and be successful at it.</p>
                                    <p><br /></p>
                                    <blockquote class="ql-align-center">We pride ourselves as beings with free will and not slaves to our instincts.</blockquote>
                                    <p><br /></p>
                                    <p>Self-hypnosis is one way to prove this to ourselves.</p>
                                    <p id="second" style="margin-top:-50px;margin-bottom:100px;">
                                    </p>
                                    <h2>WHAT IS SELF HYPNOSIS?</h2>
                                    <p><br /></p>
                                    <img src="~/Content/Images/watchaa.jpg" />
                                    <p><br /></p>
                                    <p>Self-hypnosis is the result of a <strong>self-induced hypnotic state.</strong></p>
                                    <p><br /></p>
                                    <p>A self-hypnotic state is a state of mind that increases <strong>self-suggestibility</strong>. &nbsp;</p>
                                    <p><br /></p>
                                    <p>There is no hoax or trick involved in self-hypnosis. It is not a magical imaginary power that some people have and others don’t. It is simply a process of thinking that can be very clearly explained, understood, and carried out.</p>
                                    <p><br /></p>
                                    <div style="border:5px solid rgba(40,50,60,1);">
                                        <div style="background-color:rgba(40,50,60,1); color:white;padding:5px;"><p style="color:white;"><strong>There are three main types of self-hypnosis:</strong></p></div>
                                        <p><br /></p>
                                        <div style="padding:10px;">
                                            <ul>
                                                <li><strong>Concentration Hypnosis:</strong></li>
                                            </ul>
                                            <p><br /></p>
                                            <p><em>This is similar to the most fundamental method of transcendental meditation. The idea is to focus exclusively on an idea central to the motivation of the self-hypnosis, like a mantra.</em></p>
                                            <p><br /></p>
                                            <ul>
                                                <li><strong>Inclusive Hypnosis:</strong></li>
                                            </ul>
                                            <p><br /></p>
                                            <p><em>This is what I like to call zero-focus meditation. This is more or less the opposite of meditation and can be best described by a relaxed control over the flow and passage of thoughts.</em></p>
                                            <p><br /></p>
                                            <ul>
                                                <li><strong>Visual Hypnosis</strong></li>
                                            </ul>
                                            <p><br /></p>
                                            <p><em>This is similar to a combination of the two described above. The hypnosis exercise is entirely visual and takes place in the mind eye. Instead of repeating a suggestive phrase, you imagine specific outcomes in vivid detail.</em></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div><p><br /></p>
                                    <p>Unlike meditation, <strong>these types of self-hypnosis encourage activation of the cortex</strong> – the higher thinking region of the brain.</p>
                                    <p><br /></p>
                                    <p id="third" style="margin-top:-50px;margin-bottom:100px;">
                                    </p>
                                    <h2>HOW DOES CONCENTRATION HYPNOSIS WORK?</h2>
                                    <p><br /></p>
                                    <p>Concentration hypnosis requires a fixation upon an idea. For instance, you could repeat a sentence with a suggestive quality such as:</p>
                                    <p><br /></p>
                                    <blockquote class="ql-align-center">“Every day, in every way, I’m getting better and better”</blockquote>
                                    <p><br /></p>
                                    <p>During transcendental meditation, people usually focus and listen to the sound and sensation of the breath. This allows them to <strong>drain all the noise from their mind so they can think more clearly</strong>.</p>
                                    <p><br /></p>
                                    <p><strong>During concentration hypnosis, thinking more clearly is not the goal</strong>. The goal is to increasingly embody the suggestive phrase, cumulatively, after multiple sessions.</p>
                                    <p>There are no overnight miracles!</p>
                                    <p><br /></p>
                                    <p>The repetitive suggestion is not something to listen to while the noise drains away – instead, it is something to proactively repeat in your mind with utter focus.</p>
                                    <p><br /></p>
                                    <p><strong>Your peripheral thoughts will be exploding with imagery and ideas</strong> as you keep activating the cortex with this meaningful suggestive phrase.</p>
                                    <p><br /></p>
                                    <img src="~/Content/Images/dbhsfhadfhdfhz.jpg" />
                                    <p><br /></p>

                                    <p>The patterns of neural activation that are repeatedly stimulated while your brain is stuck in this loop will be strengthened during your sleep. Over time, the phrase will become a more connected constellatory construct in the mind.</p>
                                    <p><br /></p>
                                    <p><span style="background-color: white;">This method is based on the belief that any idea exclusively occupying the mind turns into reality – to the extent that the idea is within the realm of possibility.</span></p>
                                    <p id="third2" style="margin-top:-50px;margin-bottom:100px;">
                                    </p>
                                    <h2>HOW DOES INCLUSIVE HYPNOSIS WORK?</h2>
                                    <p><br /></p>
                                    <p>Inclusive hypnosis is a similar state of mind, without the suggestive phrase. The concentration is relinquished and the control is relaxed as far as possible.</p>
                                    <p><strong>Thoughts that enter the mind are not to be consciously directed or controlled. </strong></p>
                                    <p><br /></p>
                                    <p>
                                        The direction and control of cortical thought are understood to be associated with the <strong>thalamus.</strong> The thalamus is a forebrain region in the <strong>diencephalon</strong>. Fundamentally, it relays sensory information to
                                        the cortex.
                                    </p>
                                    <p><br /></p>
                                    <p>All the surrounding regions of the brain are thalamus influences that together control the context-driven passage and direction of thought. The most prominent influence is the frontal cortex.</p>
                                    <p><br /></p>
                                    <p><strong>It is the frontal cortex that we want to relax during inclusive hypnosis.</strong> Allowing thoughts and feelings to move around the brain instinctively can allow us to calibrate and learn more about the self.</p>
                                    <p><br /></p>
                                    <p><strong>Understanding the self is the key to self-suggestibility through inclusive hypnosis.</strong></p>
                                    <p><br /></p>
                                    <p>Inclusive hypnosis is a fantastic exercise to use in addition to concentration hypnosis. The two of them go hand in hand.</p>
                                    <p><br /></p>
                                    <p>
                                        After a short session of concentration hypnosis, you can release your focus and allow noise to build up in the mind. Let your mind wander through and imagine all those things associated with the hypnotic suggestion you were repeating.
                                    </p>
