            <p>Nationwide social lockdown measures reduce the human workforce causing disruptions to supply. In some instances, the demand increases as a result of the disruption, as seen in the agricultural industry. In other cases, the reduction in human activity reduces the demand, where supply is plentiful - such is the case for the oil and aviation industries:</p>
